## AI-Assisted Code

AI-generated or AI-assisted code is allowed but held to a higher review bar.

**Disclosure is required.** If any part of your PR was written or meaningfully shaped by an AI tool (Copilot, Claude, Cursor, ChatGPT, etc.), say so in the PR description. A single line is fine:

```
AI assistance: Claude used for initial implementation of X, reviewed and modified by author.
```

**You are responsible for what you submit.** Disclosing AI use does not reduce your accountability for the code. You must understand every line you submit — we will ask questions during review and expect you to answer them. "The AI wrote it" is not an acceptable response to a review comment.

**What to watch for before submitting AI-generated code:**
- Hallucinated function signatures or package names that compile but behave incorrectly
- Logic that looks plausible but violates an invariant in [`docs/kimitsu-invariants.md`](docs/kimitsu-invariants.md)
- Tests that pass trivially without actually covering the behavior
- HTTP contract changes that break conforming implementations

PRs where AI-generated code has clearly not been reviewed will be closed without merge.

